  "text": "Timed automata, defined in [CITATION_1] , and its extension to probabilistic setting ( [CITATION_2] ) are the most commonly used formalisms for describing systems that evolve in real-time. The use of timing constraints to describe the behaviour of the system is both intuitive and expressive enough to capture a large class of real-time systems occurring in practice, and yet many of the decision problems for these models have moderate computational complexity.",
